{"key":"post-12773811","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>12773811</id>\n<content>Toss it out and start over.&amp;nbsp; You can't fix what's broken, and since you've already said you have 10% busted kernels, you're already screwed.&amp;nbsp; If I see ten busted kernels in a batch, I freak out.&amp;nbsp; Ten percent is unheard of if the rye is properly prepared.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Next time, rinse properly with hot water until the water drains clear, place rinsed grains in hot water with gypsum for 4 to 24 hours, boil ten minutes and strain/shake until the grains are dry before you load the jars or bags.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Doing the above will give zero burst kernels and the grains will all separate from each other by gravity alone.&amp;nbsp; You can't fix what's already broken when it comes to grains.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Please stop flaming those trying to help.&amp;nbsp; It never pays to be in a hurry when it's going to be a month or more before you get your mushrooms anyway.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>12773680</prev>\n<first>12773035</first>\n<last>12773811</last>\n<when>1277065188</when>\n<utime>06/20/10 11:19 PM</utime>\n</post>"}